<br>
At the very early stages you can drop 2 O'keil's buffs on the new character and let them run around with an 8 point DS.<br>
<br>
Once an 8 point DS is not sufficient to kill at a quick enough pace, you can use you flux staff to hold aggro on a MOB as your PL-ee beats on it for 50%+ damage then you finish it off.<br>
<br>
First I have heard of it, but the nuke to near death/run and abscond/gate out should work.<br>
<br>
Eventually they will get to a level where they will be able to get exp when grouped with you.  At this point you should chose MOBs to kill that are non-green to them and green to you.  Then when you kill them none of the exp will go to you and all exp plus grouping bonus will go to them.  Figured this one out while helping to teach someone to quad in a couple different areas: they were getting more exp on mobs that were green to me than when they were light blue.<br>
<br>
